content:
How search works for knowledge articles depends on your use of search options, search terms, wildcards, and operators. Salesforce Knowledge search uses the same custom search algorithms that are available throughout Salesforce.

Salesforce Knowledge is available in Essentials and the Unlimited Edition with Service Cloud. It is also available for an additional cost in: Professional, Enterprise, Performance, and Developer Editions.

Many factors influence the order in which articles appear in the results list. Some of these factors include:

Operators—When you don’t specify an operator in your article search, the search engine determines the best operator to use. The default operator is “AND”, where all terms must match.

Frequency—This algorithm calculates the frequency with which a term appears within each article.

Relevancy—Articles that are frequently viewed or attached to cases appear higher in the results. Article ownership and recent activity also boost an article in the results list.
Proximity of Terms—Articles that contain all keywords in a search are ranked highest, followed by articles with fewer keywords.

Exact Matches—Matches on exact keywords are ranked higher than matches on synonyms or lemmatized terms.
Title Field—If any search terms match words in an article title, the article is boosted in the search results.
title: Understanding Salesforce Knowledge Search
